caption: Fabulous! All of it!
Jack Rose brunch is amazing. Discount veuve clicquot bottles coupled with delicious food, great service and good vibes!!

Uh-oh 🔥❤️🥳🤩💖🔥 This is the place to go when you want to unwind, enjoy an eclectic type of vibe and are accustomed to top rate customer service. The food here is beyond incredible! The desserts? Are WAY underpriced! THE DESSERTS SHOULD COST A BILLION DOLLARS BECAUSE THEY TASTE LIKE A BILLION DOLLARS! THE MIXED DRINKS AND WINE LIST IS EXQUISITE! A MUST TO EXPLORE AND TRY IS THE FRIED CHICKEN PARMESAN! I'VE NEVER HAD A DISH LIKE THIS BEFORE! 🤩 This place is an entirely different vibe! If you are tourist you've got to put this on your MUST list! If you're a local, and haven't been here before.. then you haven't been to the best of the best in New Orleans! Our waitress Emily was beyond courteous and attentive and not for a loss of direction and advice! I'm telling you, this place out does it's reputation! 💯💯💯💯
As unique of a NOLA dinning experience as you can get! Call ahead for reservations due to Covid19.  Great food and great staff!!

So Bougie... WE LOVED IT!!! So many beautiful dining rooms that you can see from every angle so no matter what room you’re seated in you get the benefit of seeing all of them. The food was very good. They surprised us by bringing out a free champagne “bong”... we don’t drink champagne so I felt bad wasting that... but the drinks we did order were amazing. Me and my friend ended up having a horrible fight and I felt so bad for our friendly servers who never stopped being charming even though we must’ve made it so awkward lol (and sorry guys).

You can probably already tell from the amount of good reviews they have here that this is a must go in NOLA. Everything from food (classics to creatives), service, cocktails and overall aesthetic is perfection. Creative dishes meet good southern cooking. Jack Rose is a cozy homey environment that you also want to dress up and have fun in. Somehow it’s all of these things wrapped up in one.
Simply amazing and in my opinion one of the best restaurants in New Orleans
One of the best places in NOLA. every single appetizer is unique and delicious.

We celebrated NYE @ Jack Rose and it was superb-  the food was delicious, our waitress (unfortunately i can’t remember her name) was amaZing, helpful and fun.  The vibe was exactly what we were looking for.  Drinks were nice and strong.  Gots to go back and will 💅🏽
Spectacular.
Fun and exciting atmosphere. Great food choice and drinks as well.
Food is amazing! The chef is so creative and Jesse is an outstanding server! Highly recommend.

The restaurant is beautiful. The food was perfectly cooked; however, based on what we ordered, we felt that some of the dishes could have benefited from being simpler. Let scallops (that were cooked beautifully) shine and skip the cream. If you order a cheesecake (albeit one that is stated to come with chocolate) there should be some actual cheese (and perhaps shouldn't more closely resemble a mousse or pot de crème). There is an argument to be made for ordering different dishes. My mother's fish on papillote was delicious and far better for the relative lack of accoutrements. The service was ok, but became noticeably better after we ordered alcohol (this is a pet peeve of mine: you should treat your guests the same if they order Dom or tap water). All in all, I may go back to try more but was relatively disappointed in our first outing here.

As the first restaurant I visited in NOLA I didn't know what to expect. I opted into the Christmas course meal and enjoyed everything I was served. The beef cheeks, gumbo, scallops and bread pudding were all great. If I lived in the area I'd consider coming back.
Great service and better food. Great way too spend Christmas afternoon! You can't go wrong with anything on the menu.
Great!

Read the reviews. The food is presented nice but very tasteless and bland at best.  The calamari is the worse anybof us has ever tasted and why peanut butter as a sauce.  The chef must be a wack job to think these things are fancy and taste good.  The owner is insane for allowing this.  No one goes here a second time. The owner could be getting a ton of repeat business but nope they continue to disappoint everyone.  The music is so loud you have to scream to each other.  Their specialty cocktails are very poorly made. We usually get a ton of drinks at dinner but each of us barely finished one if even that.  No one took their food to go even because it was so blah even though it was very expensively over priced.

The food was AWESOME! And packed full of flavor! Our server Julia was GREAT!! We will definitely be back again! Visiting for my girlfriend birthday...the staff was super friendly and knowledgeable about the Menu items.

The flavor and quality of the food is immaculate! The service is top notch. 10/10 will visit again!  FYI If you will have a party of 6+, get the disco ball for you alcoholic drink.  The veal entree: very tender and full of flavor. Probably the best dish on the menu! The calamari appetizer: can be shared between 2 ppl and is fried. The sauce may be spicy. The Scallop and fettuccine pasta: Very flavorful the pasta includes squid ink. Delicious 😋 The potato side: It can be shared with up to 3 ppl. The potatoes are lightly salted with a slight crunch on the outside. The broccoli and cheese appetizer: Dijon mustard on the bottom, broccoli in the middle, and melted cheese on top. It was surprisingly delicious. The flounder entree: It was baked in a bag like a boil, but there wasn't much flavor. The chicken and spaghetti entrée: the chicken is fried and placed on a separate plate. The sauce is separated from the spaghetti, so nothing gets soggy. Definitely #2 on the menu. The sauce was very robust and full of flavor.
A beautiful place for brunch just beautiful with great tasting food. I Loved this place. This is a must go to in New Orleans.

Atmosphere was great  and service was great but unfortunately the food was not. Was not the food expected from a classic New Orleans restaurant on top of the price. We travel for food and this by far was a let down.
Really fun ambiance that made for a great girls night out. The disco punch was a big hit!
All of the food and drinks were amazing but the chicken and waffles were fabulous
The food we were served was good and the staff was very pleasant and attentive.
The staff were very pleasant even with their mask on, they were on point. atmosphere is NOLA. Loved that everyone had a good time ❤.
Best Brunch Ever

I'd give the food a 5 but the temperature check is ridiculous.   Of course we were fine but you can have fever from dehydration or any number of other things besides COVID-19. The people doing these checks aren't medical professionals.
This place is a beaut. Food was tasty and the servers were super pleasant!
Beautiful Ambiance,  healthy food
THE place for Sunday brunch...crispy shrimp and grits, and pompano en papillote are excellent.  And don't forget the chambongs!  Our server, Jesse, was the best!
Desert
Loved it!! Great food
Food excellent

Delicious food and great cocktails in a unique and fun atmosphere. One of my favourite stops in NOLA!  I recommend making a reservation as they did not have a table for us, but they do allow you to dine in their waiting room/entrance area full of unique art and couches.

We celebrated my birthday here, and my girlfriend and I were blown away. The restaurant is so well-decorated that you're enchanted from the moment you walk in the door. The staff was awesome. Can't remember our waiter's name, but he was wonderful. Everything tasted like heaven. That pork belly is to die for.
Fabulous food and excellent service.  Will definitely be back!

If you want to eat somewhere with character, unlike any place you've ever eaten that also has good food and friendly service, this is the place. I went as part of a group of more than 30 people on a night that they are normally closed. I heard members of our party, most of which were from out of town, talking about bringing friends and family back thre next time they're in New Orleans. It's one of those places that you just have to go to.
Great Energy!

I didn't take photos of the food because it looked so good that I needed to devour it immediately.  Walk through the front door of the hotel and make a right, up two steps.  You'll know when you've arrived.  Loved the eclecticism of the place. It's definitely reflected in the food. Everything looks random, but somehow works together perfectly. The ambiance is cozy yet energetic (how did you pull this off?). Our server was hilarious and attentive. Brought out a delicious banana bread pudding on the house to celebrate my wife's birthday.  Thank you for an awesome experience and a delicious meal.

I recently ate at Jack Rose for Sunday brunch, and it did NOT disappoint! The corned beef hash was superb! My party also had the Chicken and Waffles which was excellent! We were a little concerned about the price point, but it is definitely worth it! The portion sizes match the prices! The ambiance was very quintessential New Orleans with a little hint of Miami Art Deco! Our server was very accommodating as well which only enhanced our experience! I would definitely recommend Jack Rose for everyone to experience!
If you haven't visited before it's a must. Very nice and a place to be if you are a social butterfly!!!
Good food and great service!

First off... My waitress was a wizard and the hostess was a professor at Hogwarts.  Straight up magical all knowing beings.  The hostess had so many great suggestions and answered every question we had about the menu.  My waitress was just as talented.  She's used her powers to make sure I got the last Wagyu steak. 🤤🤤🤤 Now the meal started with the delicious romanesco in hummus appetizer. We also enjoyed a couple of champbongs.  Service immaculate, ambience artistic, food flavorsome & luscious!
Fantastic food, very nice decor and fantastic cocktails. A bit on the pricey side, but worth the money.
Very eclectic spot.  A mishmash of interesting art and decor.  Food was outstanding.
Beautiful and chic atmosphere. Food and drinks are incredible. Great location for a birthday dinner!
Highly recommended! Endless Summer + duck gumbo (fantastic) + Gulf Snapper. Excellent service from Bailey!

Food was extremely overpriced for no reason at all. The roasted cauliflower was between $8-9 dollars and for that you got a 1/4th of a head of cauliflower. At the grocery store you can buy three entire heads for that amount. The shrimp in muddy waters had good flavor but for $14 dollars you should get more than THREE shrimp. And don’t get me started on the mushroom entree...just disappointing for $20 something dollars🤦🏽‍♀️. We should’ve gotten the chicken parm like everyone else🥴. The ambiance was nice but unfortunately, we still left extremely dissatisfied. The best thing about the restaurant was the Brussels sprouts and our server Jonah.
The food and atmosphere was amazing. I had the chicken and waffles. Some of the best fried chicken I've had and the syrup had spicy pepper in it. Delicious.

I have officially learned about a new level of hospitality. Taught by none other than the hostess with the mostest, Emery Whalen, an extremely talented young entrepreneurial restauranteur with a world of opportunity yet to conquer.
Scallops were the best!!!
Good food with good service. Great location and great eclectic ambiance. Excellent drinks and their take on chicken parmesan was awesome.
Try the scallops and ink squid pasta. Amazing
Awesome staff, awesome food!

This is an awesome restaurant with great food and amazing service. The decor is unique and i love it. The food is nothing short of amazing with great taste and tenderness in every bite. The service is AMAZING, the servers are friendly and always smiling. The prices are very fair, not overpriced. I have absolutely nothing bad to say about this place, but i do say...you must check it out!!!
The food was amazing and the atmosphere makes you want to stay for hours. They keep your table tidy throughout your visit and make sure your water glass is always full!!
Food,service and ambiance...great
Amazing food

I’ve had the pleasure of dining here on two separate occasions. Once for a luncheon and another time for dinner. Both times left me with a great impression. The food and service was incredible both times. I loved it so much, I’m having dinner there again tomorrow. I’ll update my review if I have a different experience, but I’m not expecting anything less.
Awesome service spectacular food...beyond description. Loved it.
It was very disappointing. Thanksgiving day menu of turkey and dressing was very dry turkey roulade and it was tasteless. Difficult day to judge a restaurant so will try one more time.
Amazing people great venue exceptional service
Solid brunch spot.  Incredible waiting spot while they prep your table.  Staff was awesome.  Great art adorning the wall.

Food was excellent and service was great. Great place to go with a group of friends or for a romantic night with your significant other. Has a good menu to try a variety of creole dishes. With or with out meat. I personally had the veal chop, that I absolutely loved. It was prepared and cooked perfect in my opinion. I myself was the Designated driver and therefore stuck to water but being that I was with a group for a friend's birthday party I was able to witness a variety of drinks ordered and enjoyed from beers, to cocktails, and glasses if wine with no complaints. I would definitely recommend.
Great Friday Brunch.
Best Southern fried chicken in New Orleans
Good food
Love this place for food and drinks. The music here is just perfect
I tried the gumbo, banana foster, and carrot cake. I loved every bite.
Lots of excellent food and beverages were consumed. Will bring the kids back for their own mile high pie in the future
Just wow. Wow. Wow. Gluten-free friendly!
Some of the best service ever! MC did a great job getting us what we want and teaching us how to use the chambongs! Great atmosphere and awesome staff. The good was delicious too!
Love the appetizers and cocktails
The ambiance is exactly what one expects from NOLA. The food was delicious and the service excellent!
Never a wrong idea to celebrate with a Champbong and Mike High Pie
Lackluster. The descriptions on the menu were more interesting than the actual dishes. The decor is overwrought.

Food: 7/10 Service: 10/10 Decor: 8/10  Service: Let me start with an amazing service. Just great! Ann was really cool and knowledgeable.  Food: I ordered crispy shrimps - breading has taste a lot of baking powder. Ann was happy to change it to royal shrimp appetizer and that was just outstanding. Duck as main was great, as well as short rib and fettuccini nero just amazing. Brussels sprouts  too sour.  Decor: Please, please, please! Remove that ugly plastic flowers as a centerpiece. It is 21st century! And it is tacky.
Didn't get a good dinner here, don't know if the kitchen was slammed r it was just a bad night. However the restaurant is beautiful. Very nice layout.
(Translated by Google) Everything is exquisite!  (Original) Tout est exquis!

This was my husband and I’s second time dining here. First time was a month ago and we would give it 4.5 or 5 stars. Service was excellent and food was delicious. So when we came back into town for our anniversary weekend, we immediately set up a reservation. The second dining experience was pretty disappointing to say the least. Service was slow. Like over 10 minutes waiting at our table with no one checking on us when we first sat down until I asked the hostess if we had a designated waiter. Then we waited again for over 10 minutes when our plates were cleared and we just wanted our check. Our waiter did not follow up with drinks or check on food quality. Pork belly appetizer was good but it was served to us cold.  It really wasn’t that busy either..it was a Sunday night. Not sure if it was just an off night but we probably won’t come back again.
Great meal
Amazing. Place just keeps getting better and better.
Food was very good.  Had a birthday celebration there.  The whole place sang happy birthday.   It was cool.
Tasty food! Good service. Weird dessert.
Meal was wonderful. Service outstanding. Excellent place to spend a wonderful evening

(Translated by Google) A very authentic and beautiful concept. I liked it a lot I hope you like it.  (Original) Ein sehr authentisches und schönes Konzept. Es hat mir sehr gut gefallen Ich hoffe es gefällt euch.

(Translated by Google) The concept is spectacular and the presentations are outstanding. They will love it.  (Original) Das Konzept ist spektakulär und die Präsentationen sind hervorragend. Sie werden es lieben.
Everything was wonderful with the exception of the hostesses being rude amd pretentious. Food and decor was spot on. Waitress was amazing!

This is and will forever be the only place I go to enjoy delicious, mouth watering, well paired, perfection!!!! The atmosphere is fancy with slights of promiscuity; tastefully done. The staff radiate confidence  while still remaining in the background as to allow your own experience to flourish just like your tastebuds will do. Bailey specifically knows the ends and outs and her personality beams with a joy that makes you want to try everything on the menu and then some, she has a way with words. If possible I suggest you request her. She can handle small parties with rambunctious goblins ( my six month old son ) or guide you and an entire brunch/dinner party through an exploratory tasteful adventure filled with explosions and paired dishes that will literally blow your mind.  Also if she suggests a dessert, take the suggestion. She’s knows something we don’t and whatever it is, it’s magic.  Whether you’re visiting or you reside here in New Orleans this is the place, just go and thank me later!!!
Fantastic food, place is amazing.
Pretty good , soft shell shrimp app amazing and the doube

The atmosphere was amazing! The food was even better! We had the chartuiere board, duck confit hash, & steak & eggs!! Everything was so delicious! The service was great! Definitely highly recommended!
Fun and fabulous food

Horrible experience booking my birthday celebration. Upon booking the reservation I was told incorrect information by a person who could not speak clear English (Hostess named Arnette). I needed to modify the reservation to add more people. Which Arnette told me I can do 48 hours in advance. I was told 2 days before my birthday dinner that I wouldn’t be able to be accommodated. The only option I had was to cancel the entire dinner. If you can’t accommodate all of my guests then I won’t dine with you. Am I gonna tell those 4 people that they can’t come? HELL NO! The manager that I spoke with was very “brash”. I was disappointed and I had never eaten there before and at this point will never eat there!!!
Very nice Atmosphere and food was great
Good vibes, good atmosphere. And the food is sooooo good.
The service was great!!! Our waitress gave some great recommendations on what to get!! I love the champagne flute and the food plus the desserts .the place is nice and well decorated
Nothing bad to say about this place.  1st class.
Beautiful decor! Great brunch and cocktails!!
Food and drinks were delicious. I had a few specialty drinks and the redfish course.
Very nice relaxing place. Wonderful decor.
Loved it. Best service I had in NOLA
Eclectic decor. Food was fantastic.  Service was great!

The place is a very bougie instragram type of place but the food is actually really good for this atmosphere where it usually lacks.  The brunch offers a lot of choices with their "bottomless" champagne (stops when you stop eating) this is a great time for brunch and drinks in general.  Tried over 5-6 dishes and didn't hate a single one, most are large enough to share with another person.
Amazing

This place is filled with ambience! Staff was vibrant,cocktails were great and the vibe was fun. Lots of photo ops and the perfect spot to celebrate a special occasion. The Food was okay, nothing left a lasting impression but everything was well cooked and came out quickly.

I came here and loved the service, drinks and food. I started with the oysters. They were some of the best oysters I ever had. I tried their champagne which came in a nice fancy weird glass. Then I proceeded to have the lamb for dinner. The lamb was very tender than vegetables with that a company name really nice overall this was a great experience.
Good atmosphere. For how busy it was service was good as well.

I’m offering 4 stars because of the overall experience with hot tin roof top, live jazz bar downstairs, and very cool NOLA ambiance/ paintings inside the actual Jack Rose restaurant. Just the restaurant alone I would rate 3 stars as the food is a little inconsistent. The soft shell crab they served at one point was my go to, but since then it’s been hit and miss. The staff is friendly, great good looking crowd and perfectly located. They make good old fashions and a decent wine list.
Great food unique atmosphere
Excellant food, fun funky vibe.
This place was great! Food , drinks and service were on point. Will definitely be back
Very good food and nice ambiance. Had a delicious and fun dinner.
Amazing food, service, and atmosphere!

I had the BEST experience ever everyone was great the place is beautiful the food was great the vibes was good the music was good too. I love every second I was there. The hosts Kiana and Sara were so sweet! And our waiter Jesse was the best thank you so much for the experience I will be coming back again. My 25th was perfect because of Jack Rose!
What Fun! Sunday Brunch! Food was delish (lamb chops, barbecue shrimp, crawfish toast, filet) with bottomless Veuve for a phenomenal price.

I went here for a post-rehearsal party for a wedding, and everyone seemed to have such a great time. The different rooms give it such nice flair, and the artwork is very eye-catching and interesting. Great venue!

Super loud, I would go here with a group of friends. Not really the best for dates or business. They play music too so people are constantly trying to talk over the music and others (who are talking over the music.) It was a slight annoyance but not enough to knock off a star. Over all the place is beautiful with a nice vibe and good food. No wait if you make reservations, and they have a nice lounge area perfect if you do have to wait. Great place to see and be seen.  Pro tip: Your table will not be seated unless your entire party has arrived so encourage others to be on time.
Ate there twice this week! Great food!
The perfect spot for pre-dinner drinks. The furniture, art, and service really make this a fun place to drink. The food was fine, but that’s not really why you’re here.
An excellent restaurant, I would highly recommend it and don't forget to check out the roof top bar.
Fun eclectic interior with an energetic dining room. Food is great for those who are a not picky eaters. Bottomless Veuve is  a winner!
Ate the bar menu in the funky lounge area. Great decor and nice snacks.

One of the best and most fun brunches ever! It is kinda pricey, but we 100% got our moneys worth for the bottomless Veuve Clicquot. The duck hash was heaven, the charcuterie board was amazing, and the mile high pie was bomb! Can’t wait to go back for another girls brunch!
Terrible. The service sucked, the food was even worse. Waste of time and money.
My friends and I ate lunch at Jack Rose's for the first time today, and the good, ambience  and service were outstanding....thank you, Jack Rose's for a memorable meal!!

Jack Rose was delicious and unexpected.  Was it pricey...maybe?...were the portions small...maybe?...was the wine delicious...most definitely G-money...was the service impeccable...best service I ever seent!  The rooftop bar was on par with the delicious desert...we had a blast and will be back!
Great cocktails!!!
Different atmosphere than I ever experienced.  Great food and interesting people.  The bar was packed and exciting.

Ate there tonight.  Horrible. Had pompano en papillote. Waiter couldn’t figure out how to get the fish out of the bag. No salt and pepper on table and the bland dish definitely needed it. Glass of red wine tasted like sangria. Mile high pie was not the original but better than the poor semblance of the once great Ponchartrain’s version. Having eaten here for over 50 years, I would not waste a dining opportunity here.

We were here for our NYE dinner with a large (10 people) party and it was amazing! Elegant without being stuffy. Decor was interesting. Food and drinks were delicious. Staff were accommodating and very friendly. Prices were reasonable.  I would go again without hesitation. Thank you Jack Rose!
Great food and atmosphere

I have waited a long time to try this highly rated restaurants and was so dissappointed with our experience. We spent Christmas dinner here and the menu was a prefix menu which was fine. Ambiance was great and the hostess was friendly. We could barely hear our waiter and he was not overly friendly just very to the point... I had to say "what?" After everything he said and was never asked if I wanted another beverage. The food is what we were so excited for and like I said it was a huge disappointment...kind of like the chef didn't even show up. Every dish needed major salt and every dish was room temperature (even my soup and bread pudding- everyone of the dishes we ordered should have been hot). The plates weren't even warm, they we're cold. I ordered the duck as my entree and not only was it also just room temperature, there was absolutely no sear on it to crisp it up or make it more flavorful.  At $65+ a person I really expected ALOT more! We won't be returning or recommending this restaurant.

Had Christmas dinner here, so it's possible that the chef had the day off. Everything was "just OK". I've had better seafood from Bone Fish Grill. For the price, this was a huge disappointment and would not recommend. New Orleans has much better to offer.
Okay.   Overpriced.   Not bad,  but not great for Christmas Prix Fix 4 course
One of the best brunch spots in New Orleans, hands down.
A Foodies dream

If you have not been here yet, drop what you're doing and GO NOW!! The food is amazing and the atmosphere is so wonderful. The decor is quirky and amazing. Be prepared to eat, though, as the portions are very typically Southern. Such a great place!
Very eclectic, super cool vibe spot! Love all the cool decor (especially the disco ball!). AWESOME bottomless Veuve Clicquot champagne brunch for $25 🙌🏼🙌🏼
So much fun.  Food, champagne and ambiance were wonderful.
This place was superlative. The food was out of sight, the service was smooth, and the drinks were great.
Great all around, staff went out of their way to make our anniversary special
Very Swift and Good Service..... Food is Crumxhes......Will eat there again
Swanky chic!
Amazing amazing place!
Love the tableside ceaser.
AMAZING
We had an outstanding meal in a unique setting.
Fabulous experience! It's a beautiful spot with fantastic food and drinks!
Loved it!
Delish AND fun!

Wonderful service and great food. This restaurant presents a modern take on southern food in a setting that is uniquely New Orleans. Highly recommend the Fried Chicken Parm, Black Angus Daube, Squash Blossoms, and the Mile High Cake.
Beautiful space with - inside and out. Service was attentive and knowledgeable. Manager was also very welcoming! Desserts are a must!
Great service and delicious food!!!
I love the ambiance of this restaurant. The decor and music is great. The ceasar salad is a production. The food is amazingly delicious.

Upscale dining in the Pontchartrain Hotel. They have a decent wine list (not huge, but reasonably priced). The table-prepared Cesar salad is a really fun experience. I had the day's special (soft shell crab) and duck breast, both of which were very well prepared. The dessert menu is pretty big, and they are famous for their "mile high pie", although I didn't try it

When a restaurant gets everything right, it feels like both an extraordinary feat and effortless at the same time. Things usually thought of as contradictions co-mingle.  Formal and fun. Methodical and spontaneous. Steeped in tradition and at the same time boldy innovating.  That's Jack Rose, all at once. It's an instant classic of a restaurant.

Chef Brian Landry is more than a skilled chef, he is as passionate about his guests as he is about his food.  Seriously, we have tried everything on the menu and argue which dish is our favorite, in each category.  Right now, the Octopus Carpaccio is really excellent, but if you can order the SOFT SHELLED CRAB! My staple starter is the Steak Tartare with a cracked egg on top, but you really can't go wrong with anything they serve.  Their attention to detail is above and beyond other "quality" restaurants in New Orleans and they have a superb host staff.  Ariana's smile is infectious as you walk up to the host stand and you can't help but feel like you are greeted by an old friend.  If Emery is there, you won't ever want to leave. She makes you feel so welcome and special.  If you are lucky, ask for Deborah or Jenna, as your server.  Deborah is so proficient with a fun, energetic undercurrent of joy.  Jenna is your super sweet, knowledgeable server.  Go for the food and the amazing drinks, but stop and live in the moment.  Become part of New Orleans, while at Jack Rose, you won't regret it.  Bon Appetite.
Raised the bar! Exquisite selections! Must visit! 5+ Stars! Mile High Pie! Drove 8 hrs for the pie!
Great experience, decor is fantastic  great staff, waiter Justin was top class Lamb shank was sublime and desserts are worth saving room for

I can’t say enough good things about this spot! Emery, Ariana, and John took care of our group and they were so pleasant and accommodating. It was a busy weekend because of graduation, and we didn’t have reservations. They worked us in, kept us in the loop, and they were all so positive and friendly. The food and drinks were fantastic. I will definitely be back when I visit New Orleans.
We had a very good experience. Food was delicious and our server Sara was a blast. Music is modern and I loved it, great for a baby boomer.

The decor, ambiance, and staff were all well above average. There's also a great music playlist -- eclectic and creative rock mix. I wish I could be as enthusiastic about the food. I was brought bread that was described as being "right out of the oven" that was room temp and tough. My shrimp & okra gumbo (as a Louisiana native, I'm admittedly a tough critic here) was tepid and slightly sweet(?). The Black Angus daube in the eponymous entree was tender and delicious, but the vegetable accompaniment of carrots and fingerling potatoes was uninspired and lacked seasoning to speak of. Last, the blueberry bread pudding sounded great, but also arrived room temp and dry (I've never had a bread pudding that wasn't at least warm), with the blueberries piled on the side rather than fully integrated into the dish. The wines-by-the-glass list was also a major disappointment for a restaurant of this purported caliber -- pedestrian and short on creativity, and lacking in printed details. I may give this place a second chance (the staff really was attentive and pleasant) and try some other items, but there are just too many other great restaurants in New Orleans for me to recommend Jack Rose at this point.

From cocktails in the Living Room to dinner in the dining room we loved everything. The cracked potatoes were a fabulously spicy surprise!  The paneed veal for 2 was big enough for 4 but so great I’m glad we had leftivers!   We went back twice in the same week. The food, the service and the atmosphere made it our new favorite plsce to go.

AMAZING!! My friend and i went for dinner after watching the Derby at Tin Roof. We had the most amazing meal.  3 different appetizers and each one was better then the next, which of course the new Octopus dish being the one i loved the most.  Then we moved on to our Entrees and I ordered the soft Shell Crab which was to die for and i'm normally not a soft Shell Crab Person and my friend had a pasta piccata dish that was so delectable we both finished everything on our plates.  But of course we couldn't leave with out having dessert. She had a grapefruit cake and i had this chocolate ice cream with chocolate covered raisins (mine was so good i want more) all in all this was an incredible experience and our waiter Barry made it so much more fun! thanks so much for such a great time, i can't wait to go back!!!

Jack Rose lived up to all my expectations for great food, exceptional service, and unique design, and it also nailed that rare, hard-to-define quality: it was a damn good time. The place just has a great energy and everyone around me seemed to be having a blast. That's apparent from the moment you step into the "living room," which now serves small plates along with cocktails, wine, and beer. It's a cool room (no doubt you've already seen somebody's selfie with the Lil Wayne portrait on Instagram), and it works really well as a place to hang with a group and meet other people. You could easily make a night of eating and drinking in this space. But the main attraction is the "dining room," which shares the same vibe and liveliness but with an expanded menu. The entrees are diverse (my two favorites, Pompano en Papillote and Chicken Parmesan, are a good example of this), but everything I had was successful, aka scrumptious. The dessert menu is also a real standout (Fluff-A-Nutter is all I'm saying).  Did me and my friends have too many (delicious) cocktails and a little too much fun? Probably. But I nonetheless stand by my judgement on this one: plan to have a great time, overeat, and soak in the over-the-top decor, and you will be rewarded.
Though only open five days, everything ran smoothly.  Good appetizers, flounder was flavorful.  The grapefruit cake is sensational!
